title: Crisis Management and Emergency Planning: Preparing for Today's
description:
English | ISBN: 146655505X | 2013 | 550 pages | PDF | 17 MB 

Emergency managers and officials have seen a tremendous increase in the planning responsibilities placed on their shoulders over the last decade. 

Crisis Management and Emergency Planning: Preparing for Todays Challenges supplies time-tested insights to help communities and organizations become better prepared to cope with natural and manmade disasters and their impacts on the areas they serve.
